        <content>
          <p>SECTION 2--PEREMPTION
Art. 3458.  Peremption; effect
Peremption is a period of time fixed by law for the existence of a right.  Unless timely exercised, the right is extinguished upon the expiration of the peremptive period.</p>
        </content>
